parser
Class Parser

java.lang.Object
  parser.Parser

public class Parser
extends java.lang.Object

Objects of the class Parser use the scanner.Scanner object to read and tokenize a string of inputs, then evaluates statements, expressions, terms, and factors in increasing levels of priority, according to the order of operations.

April 8, 2020

parseStatement

public Statement parseStatement()
                         throws java.lang.Exception
Method parseStatement reads the input token and begins evaluating a statement in the pascal language. A statement starts either with a print command (WRITELN), a begin block command (BEGIN), a variable/procedure declaration, an if statement (IF), or a while statement (WHILE [cond] DO [xyz]).

Throws:
java.lang.Exception - if the expected String does not match the consumed token
Returns:
the parsed statement
